A man charged with assaulting his sister has been fined Sh10,000 or two months in jail. Frederick Owour pleaded guilty to assaulting and injuring Linda Owuor on April 24 in Dagoretti Corner, Nairobi county. Prosecutor Charles Mwangi told the court that Fredrick attacked his sister after she supported their mother in a quarrel. "I did not beat my mother but I assaulted my sister causing her nose injuries," Fredrick told KiberaÂ senior principal magistrate Philip Mutua. The prosecution told the court the accused was a first-time offender. The man pleaded for forgiveness, saying he will not repeat the offence. Edited by E.Kibii